  "texts": [
    "Llama 2, with its emphasis on scalability and efficient data usage, illustrates the potential for designing models that are both high-performing and less prone to inheriting biases from their training datasets.",
    "The findings underscore the importance of a multifaceted approach to model development, where considerations of fairness are integrated at every stage of the design and training process.",
    "However, the study also highlights the absence of a one-size-fits-all solution to bias mitigation, pointing to the necessity of modelspecific strategies.",
    "The insights gained from this comparison advocate for the continued exploration of innovative methods to enhance both the accuracy and fairness of LLMs.",
    "In light of these results, future research should focus on developing adaptive, context-aware models that can dynamically adjust to minimize bias while maintaining high levels of performance."
  ],
